  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON The proposed single storey side extension by reason of its size, scale, position considerably further forward than the original building line and projecting main entrance will undermine the symmetry of main building, fail to remain subservient to the main building, spoil the architectural character of the building to the detriment of the streetscene, visual amenity and the character and appearance of the surrounding Hillmarton Conservation area.  The proposed works would therefore fail to comply with policy 12 of the NPPF (2012); policies 7.4, 7.6 7.8 of the London Plan (2012) and policy CS12 of the UDP, policies D4, D11, D22 and D26 of the UDP; draft policies DM1 and DM3 of the Development Management Policies (Submission Document 2012); and the requirements of the Conservation Area Design Guide (2002) and the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006)."
